<div class="story"> <p>Ocean Dunes is an oceanfront subdivision in the heart of downtown Duck with shopping and dining within walking distance. The 91 building lots, mostly built already, line Christopher Dr and the 5 small cu-de-sacs. Even though the roads are private and there is a beach access, there is no active home owners association and no HOA Fee. You can find Ocean Dunes off of Rte 12, sandwiched between the communities of <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/poteskeet.asp" title="Poteskeet">Poteskeet</a> to the north and <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/seapines.asp" target="Seapines">Seapines</a> to the south. </p>     <p><a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/ocean-dunes-covenants.pdf" title="Ocean Dunes covenants" target="_blank">Ocean Dunes covenants</a> <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/duck/ocean-dunes-bylaws.pdf" title="Ocean Dunes By Laws">Ocean Dunes By Laws</a>    - - - <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/Covenant-Disclaimer.asp" target="_blank"><b>    *</b></a></p>
